WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.080 --> 00:00:05.330
(gentle flowing music)

00:00:10.110 --> 00:00:13.940
- Hello, everyone, and welcome
back to English with Lucy.

00:00:13.940 --> 00:00:18.070
Today I am going to show
you six everyday habits

00:00:18.070 --> 00:00:21.310
for improving your English,
and these are things

00:00:21.310 --> 00:00:23.710
that you can do at home.

00:00:23.710 --> 00:00:25.630
One of the best ways to learn a language

00:00:25.630 --> 00:00:28.290
is to make it a part of your daily life.

00:00:28.290 --> 00:00:31.660
And you need to do this by forming habits.

00:00:31.660 --> 00:00:34.110
And I have got some great ideas for you.

00:00:34.110 --> 00:00:37.340
Some of these habits are really enjoyable.

00:00:37.340 --> 00:00:39.600
For example, the first one, which is

00:00:39.600 --> 00:00:43.930
perform guided meditation in English.

00:00:43.930 --> 00:00:46.120
So guided meditation is great

00:00:46.120 --> 00:00:49.630
for relieving stress levels and anxiety

00:00:49.630 --> 00:00:52.200
and making you feel more
connected with yourself,

00:00:52.200 --> 00:00:54.890
but doing it in the
language you are learning

00:00:54.890 --> 00:00:58.060
can offer so many benefits.

00:00:58.060 --> 00:01:02.040
Often listening to English,
trying to understand English,

00:01:02.040 --> 00:01:04.200
learning English in general is really,

00:01:04.200 --> 00:01:06.430
really stressful for students.

00:01:06.430 --> 00:01:10.470
But guided meditation sessions
are designed to relax you,

00:01:10.470 --> 00:01:14.400
so you may find yourself
picking up on a lot more.

00:01:14.400 --> 00:01:16.740
I have got three recommendations

00:01:16.740 --> 00:01:21.300
for great YouTube channels
that offer guided meditation.

00:01:21.300 --> 00:01:24.160
The first speaks with a British accent,

00:01:24.160 --> 00:01:26.530
the second with an American accent,

00:01:26.530 --> 00:01:28.510
and the third with an Australian accent.

00:01:28.510 --> 00:01:30.850
So you can choose which is best for you.

00:01:30.850 --> 00:01:34.410
For British, we have Caroline McCready.

00:01:34.410 --> 00:01:36.431
- [Caroline] Simply become
aware of your breathing.

00:01:36.431 --> 00:01:39.181
(ethereal music)

00:01:40.150 --> 00:01:43.060
- She has got the most
beautiful voice and accent.

00:01:43.060 --> 00:01:46.730
For the American accent, we
have The Mindful Movement.

00:01:46.730 --> 00:01:49.170
- [Woman] And now turn
off all distractions

00:01:49.170 --> 00:01:51.420
and commit this time for yourself.

00:01:51.420 --> 00:01:54.270
- You can see there's so much
vocabulary to pick up on.

00:01:54.270 --> 00:01:57.470
And some people find that
listening to foreign languages

00:01:57.470 --> 00:01:59.540
in a subconscious state can help them

00:01:59.540 --> 00:02:01.420
pick up on more vocabulary.

00:02:01.420 --> 00:02:02.720
It doesn't happen for everyone,

00:02:02.720 --> 00:02:05.140
but try it and see if it works for you.

00:02:05.140 --> 00:02:07.240
And the last one, for Australian accents,

00:02:07.240 --> 00:02:09.860
we have Michael Sealey.

00:02:09.860 --> 00:02:11.900
- [Michael] And you understand that, yes,

00:02:11.900 --> 00:02:14.173
these are your thoughts,

00:02:15.810 --> 00:02:19.220
but you also know and understand

00:02:19.220 --> 00:02:22.690
that who you are is so much more

00:02:22.690 --> 00:02:24.513
than simply your thoughts.

00:02:26.190 --> 00:02:30.100
- Right? Let's move on
to habit number two.

00:02:30.100 --> 00:02:33.030
Habit number two is all
about keeping yourself

00:02:33.030 --> 00:02:36.090
inspired and motivated, okay?

00:02:36.090 --> 00:02:39.940
Something that I found so
helpful and interesting

00:02:39.940 --> 00:02:42.790
when I was actively learning Spanish

00:02:42.790 --> 00:02:47.320
was discovering other people's
language learning journeys.

00:02:47.320 --> 00:02:49.210
