00:02:49.210 --> 00:02:51.860
with other non-native English speakers

00:02:51.860 --> 00:02:54.400
who have reached a level of English

00:02:54.400 --> 00:02:56.560
that you also want to reach.

00:02:56.560 --> 00:02:58.950
Every day try and watch a video

00:02:58.950 --> 00:03:01.710
of somebody sharing their experience.

00:03:01.710 --> 00:03:04.270
You can learn so much from them.

00:03:04.270 --> 00:03:06.260
There is only so much I can teach you

00:03:06.260 --> 00:03:08.100
as a native English speaker.

00:03:08.100 --> 00:03:10.960
I'm in your shoes because
I've learned other languages,

00:03:10.960 --> 00:03:14.170
but I'm not absolutely in
your shoes with English.

00:03:14.170 --> 00:03:16.310
That's why I always say
it's great to listen

00:03:16.310 --> 00:03:18.730
to native speakers and native teachers,

00:03:18.730 --> 00:03:22.350
but also non-native teachers
because they understand

00:03:22.350 --> 00:03:25.510
where you're coming from because
they were once there too.

00:03:25.510 --> 00:03:28.010
So I've got an example for
you that I will link below.

00:03:28.010 --> 00:03:29.670
There is the most lovely girl.

00:03:29.670 --> 00:03:32.010
She's from Brazil, but she speaks English

